This paper deals with wireless networks and their transmission schemes, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses coding schemes and optimization frameworks, which are relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on cellular networks, which are studied in the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
